{{Politics of Bulgaria}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Bulgaria]] on 16 May 1971.<ref>[[Dieter Nohlen]] & Philip Stöver (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p368 {{ISBN|978-3-8329-5609-7}}</ref> Voters were asked whether they approved of a new constitution (known as the [[Zhivkov Constitution]]), whose first article noted the "leading role" of the [[Bulgarian Communist Party|Communist Party]]. The result was reportedly 99.7% in favour, with a voter turnout of 99.7%.<ref>Nohlen & Stöver, p375</ref>
