{{Politics of Mauritania}}
A '''referendum on the new [[constitution of France]]''' was held in [[Mauritania]] on 28 September 1958 as part of a [[French constitutional referendum, 1958|wider referendum]] held across the [[French Union]]. The new constitution would see the country become part of the new [[French Community]] if accepted, or result in independence if rejected. It was approved by 94.04% of voters.<ref>[http://www.sudd.ch/event.php?lang=en&id=fr011958 Frankreich, 28. September 1958 : Verfassung] Direct Democracy</ref>
