'''Prepared testimony''' is a form of [[testimony]] which is prepared ahead of time, and is then presented verbally or in writing. It is attested as true by the author(s), or given under [[oath]]. Typically it is given to a large body or organization. Questions may be posed to the attestor or [[witness]], but the [[forum (legal)|forum]] where the testimony is given may not permit this, or it may be impractical, or questioning may be cast implicitly in the form of further testimony by others.

